The idea's interesting, but I feel like there are a few assumptions that are out of place in the article. For example, the connection between SCP-3914 and . I had to re-read the article to figure out that Rubinstein is the reason that the foundation is investigating for anomalous objects from SCP-3914. It's reasonable that one or more of the members with unidentified anomalies can also create anomalous objects, but it's not very clear. I think the best way to combat this would be to put a little bit less emphasis on the what and more emphasis on the why. It's just a minor fix, so I'll give this one an upvote. +1







